      "institutionalSecret": "",
      "theRoom": "1,600 students on a 450-acre wooded campus on Massachusetts' North Shore, minutes from Gloucester and the Atlantic coast. The honor code and chapel culture produce a residential community that is intentionally formed. Gordon is the only CCCU college in New England, which gives it a regional distinctiveness: the evangelical intellectual who wants to be in the Northeast, near Boston, without the secular campus culture of Tufts or BU.",
