      "archetype": "The Nazarene Liberal Arts University on the Pacific",
      "oneSentenceSummary": "Point Loma Nazarene University is a Church of the Nazarene liberal arts university of 3,500 students on a 90-acre coastal campus overlooking the Pacific Ocean and San Diego Bay — combining a Wesleyan-Holiness Christian tradition with San Diego's healthcare, military, biotech, and creative economy.",
      "pipeline": "Nursing — top-ranked in California, feeding Sharp HealthCare, Scripps Health, Kaiser Permanente San Diego, and the naval medical infrastructure at Camp Pendleton and Balboa Naval Medical Center. Business — Fermanian School of Business placing graduates into San Diego's biotech, defense, and financial services sectors. Education — strong credentialing into San Diego Unified and surrounding districts. Communications and Media — film, journalism, and digital media production. Biology and Pre-Health Sciences — strong pre-medical and pre-dental placement. Psychology and Social Work. 3,500 undergraduates; 4,200 total enrollment.",
      "hiddenPathway": "Point Loma's most distinctive hidden asset is its intersection of military, healthcare, and biotech — three of San Diego's dominant industries — with a Christian liberal arts education. San Diego hosts the largest concentration of military personnel and veterans in the United States. PLNU's nursing and healthcare programs feed directly into the naval and military medical infrastructure. The biotech corridor along Torrey Pines Road — home to Illumina, J&J Janssen, Pfizer La Jolla, and dozens of emerging biotech firms — is 20 minutes from campus. PLNU biology and chemistry graduates enter this ecosystem through a pipeline that is disproportionate to the university's national name recognition.",
      "institutionalSecret": "The Point Loma campus may be the most physically spectacular setting of any Christian university in America — 90 acres on a peninsula above the Pacific, with views of San Diego Bay, the downtown skyline, Mexico, and the Channel Islands. The campus is a four-year living asset that students undervalue in the college search and overvalue the moment they graduate and try to replicate it.",
      "theRoom": "90-acre campus on a coastal mesa above Ocean Beach and the Point Loma peninsula. 65% of students live on campus. The student body is approximately 50% California residents, with significant representation from the Pacific Northwest, Arizona, and Hawaii. San Diego's military community sends a notable percentage of faculty and military-connected students. The Wesleyan-Holiness tradition is meaningful but not culturally restrictive — the campus is warm, communal, and mission-oriented.",
      "lifestyle": "San Diego is the most consistently livable major city in America — Mediterranean climate year-round, beaches, hiking, surfing, and a cultural depth that extends well beyond its beach city identity. The combination of the military, biotech, healthcare, and creative economy makes San Diego a genuinely excellent long-term career market for PLNU graduates who want to stay.",
      "bestFitPersonality": "High Agreeableness, Faith-motivated, Service-oriented, Healthcare or science-drawn, California or military-connected, Community-minded",
      "faithTradition": "Church of the Nazarene (Wesleyan-Holiness)",
      "geographicInfluenceRadius": "San Diego dominant — Los Angeles secondary, Pacific Northwest and Arizona, national through nursing and healthcare alumni networks, military community national reach",
      "economicOutcome": "Elite nursing placement through Sharp HealthCare, Scripps, Kaiser San Diego, and naval medical infrastructure; biology and pre-health into San Diego biotech corridor; business graduates into defense contractors and biotech; education throughout San Diego Unified",
      "gradCities": [
        "San Diego CA",
        "Los Angeles CA",
        "Phoenix AZ",
        "Portland OR",
        "Seattle WA"
      ],
