    "name": "Western Colorado University",
    "location": "Gunnison, Colorado",
    "region": "Mountain West",
    "archetype": "Outdoor Industry & Mountain Community University",
    "oneSentenceSummary": "Western Colorado University combines experiential education, mountain living, outdoor-industry leadership, environmental stewardship, and entrepreneurial flexibility to create one of the most distinctive lifestyle-oriented public universities in the American West.",
    "pipeline": "Founded in 1901, Western Colorado University serves as one of the primary talent pipelines into Colorado's outdoor recreation economy, public lands management sector, environmental industries, recreation management, education, and rural entrepreneurship ecosystems. Located in Gunnison near Crested Butte, the university leverages one of the most unique outdoor environments in North America as an extension of the classroom.",
    "hiddenPathway": "Most families see Western as a regional public university. The hidden reality is that it functions as a leadership incubator for the outdoor recreation economy. Graduates often find themselves working in outdoor brands, ski industries, recreation management, conservation organizations, tourism, environmental consulting, endurance sports, and mountain entrepreneurship.",
    "institutionalSecret": "Western's greatest asset is not academic prestige—it's lifestyle integration. Students spend four years embedded inside the exact ecosystem many people spend their careers trying to access later in life.",
    "theRoom": "Students are adventurous, independent, environmentally conscious, physically active, community-oriented, and often deeply connected to mountain culture.",
