    "oneSentenceSummary": "Montana Western is America's leading public experiential-learning university, using its unique Experience One model to immerse students in one subject at a time while preparing leaders for rural entrepreneurship, outdoor industries, education, agriculture, and community development.",
    "pipeline": "Founded in 1893, Montana Western operates one of the most distinctive educational systems in American higher education through its Experience One program, where students take a single class at a time for intensive learning. The university has developed strong pipelines into education, agriculture, natural resources, outdoor leadership, business, healthcare support professions, and rural entrepreneurship.",
    "hiddenPathway": "Most families view Montana Western as a small regional public university. The hidden reality is that its educational model develops focus, adaptability, and applied problem-solving abilities that employers consistently value. Graduates often outperform peers in practical execution and leadership because they learn by doing rather than merely studying.",
    "institutionalSecret": "Experience One may be the closest public-university equivalent to Colorado College's Block Plan. Students learn how to master complexity through total immersion rather than multitasking.",
    "theRoom": "Students are practical, independent, adventurous, community-oriented, and highly engaged in hands-on learning. Prestige matters less than competence.",
    "lifestyle": "Outdoor recreation, ranching culture, hunting, fishing, agriculture, mountain recreation, close faculty relationships, and strong community integration.",
